article.description: Andrea Riley made the go-ahead 3-pointer with 7 seconds left and Oklahoma State scored the final 12 points in a 61-58 win over Texas A&M.
article.headline: Riley caps 12-point Oklahoma State run with winner
article.linkText: Late 3-pointer lifts Oklahoma State past A&M
article.story:
COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- Andrea Riley made the go-ahead 3-pointer with 7 seconds left and Oklahoma State (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) scored the final 12 points in a 61-58 victory over Texas A&M (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 19 AP) on Saturday.

Riley, who scored 29 points, held the ball as the shot clock ticked down. She hit the shot just before time expired to put Oklahoma State (16-1, 4-0 Big 12) on top. As she excitedly ran to midcourt after the basket, her teammates jumped up and down and cheered.

The Aggies had a chance to tie it, but A'Quonesia Franklin's 3-pointer fell short.

Texas A&M (13-5, 1-3) trailed by five at halftime, but built a nine-point lead with 6:26 remaining.

But that would be the Aggies' last points. Texas A&M had three turnovers and missed a layup in that span.

The Aggies were led by Takia Starks with 16 points and Franklin had 14 points and 11 assists.

Oklahoma State outrebounded Texas A&M 48-27, helping them to 20 second-chance points. The Aggies had just four second-chance points.

Danielle Green added 14 points and eight rebounds for Oklahoma State.

Texas A&M led 10-3 early, but Oklahoma State had tied it 24-all about seven minutes before halftime. The Cowgirls outscored A&M 13-8 in the final minutes of the half to take a 37-32 halftime lead.
